Frank James Marshall vs Samuel Shapiro
Simul (1944) (exhibition), New York, NY USA
Italian Game: Evans Gambit. Lasker Defense (C52)

1. e4 e5 2. Bc4 Bc5 3. b4 Bb4 4. c3 Ba5 5. Nf3 Nc6 6. O-O d6 7. d4 Bb6 8. a4 Nf6 9. a5 Na5 10. Ra5 Ba5 11. de5 de5 12. Ne5 Be6 13. Be6 fe6 14. Qb3 Bb6 15. Ba3 c5 16. Qb5 Kf8 17. f4 Qc7 18. Nd2 Rd8 19. Ndc4 Ne4 20. f5 ef5 21. Rf5 Kg8 22. Qb3 Nd2 23. Nd2 c4 24. Qb6 Qb6 25. Kf1 Qe3 26. Be7 Qd2 27. Bd8 Qd8 28. g4 a5 29. g5 Qd1 30. Kf2 Qc2 31. Kg3 Qf5

This game is from a simul where Marshall scored +17 -1 =6. This one loss was to a high school student, 17-year old Samuel Shapiro, attending Townsend Harris Hall in Queens, NY. (Brooklyn Daily Eagle, 30 Mar 1944, p. 15)
